      • getInstance

        public static Slyce getInstance(android.content.Context context)
        Gets an instance of the Slyce SDK.

        **Important:** Slyce recommends that the instance returned from this method is used within a single thread.

        Parameters:
        context - The application context.
        Returns:
        an instance of Slyce SDK.

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes the Slyce SDK.

      • createSession

        public SlyceSession createSession()
                           throws SlyceMissingGDPRComplianceException,
                                  SlyceNotOpenedException
        Creates a new SlyceSession instance if the Slyce SDK is opened. Otherwise, a SlyceNotOpenedException is thrown.

        **Important:** If GDPR compliance is required and the user has not consented, a SlyceMissingGDPRComplianceException is thrown.

        Returns:
        a new SlyceSession instance.
        Throws:
        SlyceMissingGDPRComplianceException
        SlyceNotOpenedException

      • getDefaultSession

        @Deprecated
public SlyceSession getDefaultSession()
        Deprecated. in version 5.6.0. Please use createSession() instead.
        Gets the default instance of the SlyceSession if the Slyce SDK is opened. If the Slyce SDK has not been opened, the default session will be null. The default session can not be manually invalidated.
        Returns:
        the default SlyceSession instance.

      • isOpen

      • open

        public void open(java.lang.String accountId,
                 java.lang.String apiKey,
                 java.lang.String spaceId,
                 SlyceCompletionHandler completionHandler)
        Initializes the Slyce SDK using valid Account ID, API Key, and Space ID.

        **Important:** Successfully opening the Slyce object is mandatory before you start performing any tasks in the SDK!

        Parameters:
        accountId - The Account ID for your organization.
        apiKey - The API Key for your organization.
        spaceId - The Space ID for this SlyceInstance.
        completionHandler - The completion handler to handle callbacks for the Slyce open result. If successful, the error parameter will be null. If unsuccessful, an error will be returned.
